---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Training — Pendle Forest Orienteers"
  description="Coaching and skills training for PFO members — map reading, route choice, night orienteering and more."
>

<main id="main">

  <PageHero
    page="training"
    eyebrow="Training"
    heading="Get better at the bits you find hard."
    lede="PFO runs a regular programme of training sessions for members — informal map-reading help for newcomers, technique sessions for intermediate orienteers, and night-orienteering practice through the winter. Cath Wilson, our lead coach, plans the programme each year."
  />

  <section class="info-block">
    <div class="info-wrap text-cols">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">For newcomers</p>
        <h2>Map symbols, contours, route choice.</h2>
        <p>If you've done a couple of events and are starting to want to understand what's actually happening on the map, the newcomer-focused sessions are for you. We cover the IOF symbol set, contour reading, simple compass work, and the basic route-choice questions that come up on every course.</p>
        <p>Sessions are typically held on a weekend morning at a local park, last about 90 minutes, and are free for members. Non-members welcome too — turn up and we'll sign you up afterwards.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">For experienced orienteers</p>
        <h2>Night-O, sprint technique, JEC prep.</h2>
        <p>Once you're past the basics, our intermediate and advanced sessions focus on specific techniques — dark-conditions navigation, urban sprint pace, attack-point selection, and (for juniors aiming at JEC, EYOC and JK) team-event preparation.</p>
        <p>These are typically arranged through the members' WhatsApp group when there's enough interest. Get in touch with <a href="/contacts">Cath Wilson</a> if you want to suggest a topic.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-block alt">
    <div class="info-wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Self-led practice</p>
      <h2>Things you can work on alone.</h2>
      <div class="resources-grid">
        <div class="resource">
          <h3>Anytime orienteering</h3>
          <p>Permanent courses and MapRun loops in local parks let you practice navigation on your own schedule. <a href="/information/anytime-orienteering">See the list of permanent courses</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="resource">
          <h3>SLOW training videos</h3>
          <p>South London Orienteers have produced an excellent eight-part series on technique, presented by GB team athletes. Worth watching even on a rainy afternoon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="resource">
          <h3>Carol McNeill's books</h3>
          <p>Carol McNeill's "Orienteering" is the book most British orienteers learned from. Still relevant, well-illustrated, and available secondhand for very little.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="resource">
          <h3>RouteGadget</h3>
          <p>After every event, we upload routes and times to RouteGadget. Reviewing your route alongside the winners' route on the same map is the single best post-event learning tool.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: clamp(40px, 5vw, 80px) var(--pad-x) clamp(40px, 4vw, 64px);
  }
  .page-hero-wrap { max-width: var(--max-w); margin: 0 auto; }
  .page-hero .eyebrow { color: var(--gold-muted); margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .page-hero .eyebrow::before { background: var(--plum); }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 64px);
    line-height: 1.0;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 20;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .page-lede {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.2vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .info-block { padding: clamp(48px, 5vw, 80px) var(--pad-x); }
  .info-block.alt { background: var(--paper-2); }
  .info-wrap { max-width: var(--max-w); margin: 0 auto; }
  .info-block .eyebrow { color: var(--gold-muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .info-block .eyebrow::before { background: var(--plum); }
  .info-block h2 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 48, "SOFT" 20;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 18px 0;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .info-block h3 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 36, "SOFT" 20;
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--plum);
    padding-top: 12px;
  }
  .info-block p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 14px 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .info-block a { color: var(--navy); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--gold); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .info-block a:hover { color: var(--plum); }

  .text-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(32px, 5vw, 64px);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .text-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .resources-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 28px 36px;
  }
</style>
